    "description": "Roche India Advisory Limited is actively seeking a talented and motivated Surgeon to join our dynamic team in Pimpri-Chinchwad. This is an excellent opportunity for professionals who are passionate about making a real impact in a fast-growing organization.\n\nAbout Roche India Advisory Limited:\nRoche India Advisory Limited is a leading organization in the Remote sector, committed to excellence, innovation, and employee growth. We offer a dynamic work environment where talent is recognized and rewarded.\n\nKey Responsibilities:\n• Provide high-quality patient care and maintain patient records\n• Participate in quality improvement initiatives and clinical audits\n• Adhere to NABH/JCI accreditation standards\n• Educate patients and families on health management and disease prevention\n• Respond to medical emergencies and provide immediate care\n• Coordinate with multidisciplinary teams for comprehensive patient management\n• Monitor patient progress and adjust treatment plans accordingly\n\nRequired Skills & Qualifications:\n• B.Arch / M.Arch from recognized institution\n• 12-20 years of relevant experience\n• Proficiency in Infection Control\n• Proficiency in Medical Terminology\n• Proficiency in Patient Care\n• Proficiency in Clinical Documentation\n• Proficiency in ICD-10\n• Proficiency in Clinical Research\n• Proficiency in Telemedicine\n• Proficiency in HIPAA Compliance\n\nWork Mode: Remote - Work from anywhere in India\n\nWhat We Offer:\n• Professional development and training programs\n• International travel opportunities for senior roles\n• Meal coupons and food allowance\n• Comprehensive health insurance for self and family\n• Modern office with recreational facilities\n• Employee stock options (ESOPs) for eligible roles\n• Salary Range: 35 LPA - 70 LPA per annum\n\nLocation: Pimpri-Chinchwad, Maharashtra, India\n\nIf you are excited about this opportunity, apply now and take the next step in your career journey with Roche India Advisory Limited!",
